{
  "title": "ISic001189. Haluntium honours the son of Timandros",
  "body": "<div id=\"editions\"><div class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag, Norma Quagliana</div><div id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"grc\">  <div class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\"><span class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  <a id=\"al1-interpretive\"><!--0--></a><span class=\"linenumber\">1</span><span dir=\"ltr\">(vac.4)</span><span data-text=\"ὁ\" data-n=\"10\" data-lemma=\"\">ὁ</span>  <span data-text=\"δᾶμος\" data-n=\"15\" data-lemma=\"\">δᾶμος</span>  <span dir=\"ltr\">(vac.3)</span>  <br id=\"al2-interpretive\"><span class=\"linenumber\">2</span><span data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Βίωτον Τιμάνδρου\"><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Βίωτον\"><span data-text=\"Βίωτον\" data-n=\"25\" data-lemma=\"\">Β̣ίωτον</span></span>  <span data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Τιμάνδρου\"><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"patronym\" data-text=\"Τιμάνδρου\"><span data-text=\"Τιμάνδρου\" data-n=\"30\" data-lemma=\"\">Τιμάνδρο[υ]</span></span></span></span>  <br id=\"al3-interpretive\"><span class=\"linenumber\">3</span><span data-text=\"εὐνοίας\" data-n=\"35\" data-lemma=\"\">εὐνοίας</span>  <span data-text=\"ἕνεκεν\" data-n=\"40\" data-lemma=\"\">ἕνεκεν̣</span>  </span></div>  <p class=\"miniapp\"></p></div><div class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag, Norma Quagliana</div><div id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"grc\"><div class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\"><span class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\"><a id=\"al1-diplomatic\"><!--0--></a><span class=\"linenumber\">1</span> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <span data-text=\"ὁ\" data-n=\"10\" data-lemma=\"\">Ο</span><span data-text=\"δᾶμος\" data-n=\"15\" data-lemma=\"\">ΔΑΜΟΣ</span> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <br id=\"al2-diplomatic\"><span class=\"linenumber\">2</span><span data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Βίωτον Τιμάνδρου\"><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Βίωτον\"><span data-text=\"Βίωτον\" data-n=\"25\" data-lemma=\"\">.ΙΩΤΟΝ</span></span><span data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Τιμάνδρου\"><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"patronym\" data-text=\"Τιμάνδρου\"><span data-text=\"Τιμάνδρου\" data-n=\"30\" data-lemma=\"\">ΤΙΜΑΝΔΡΟ[.]</span></span></span></span><br id=\"al3-diplomatic\"><span class=\"linenumber\">3</span><span data-text=\"εὐνοίας\" data-n=\"35\" data-lemma=\"\">ΕΥΝΟΙΑΣ</span><span data-text=\"ἕνεκεν\" data-n=\"40\" data-lemma=\"\">ΕΝΕΚΕ.</span></span></div><p class=\"miniapp\"></p></div></div>  <div id=\"facsimile-images\"><h2>Facsimile Images</h2><a href=\"ISic001189_text_tiled.tif\"><img title=\"Photo J. Prag, 2022-05-23, courtesy  Museo Archeologico Regionale Antonino Salinas\" src=\"ISic001189_text_tiled-thumb.tif\"></a><a href=\"ISic001189_text.jpg\"><img title=\"Photo J. Prag, 2022-05-23, courtesy  Museo Archeologico Regionale Antonino Salinas\" src=\"ISic001189_text-thumb.jpg\"></a><a href=\"ISic001189_tiled.tif\"><img title=\"Photo J. Prag, courtesy  Museo Archeologico Regionale Antonino Salinas\" src=\"ISic001189_tiled-thumb.tif\"></a><a href=\"ISic001189.jpg\"><img title=\"Photo J. Prag, courtesy  Museo Archeologico Regionale Antonino Salinas\" src=\"ISic001189-thumb.jpg\"></a><a href=\"ISic001189_rightthreequarter_tiled.tif\"><img title=\"Photo J. Prag, courtesy  Museo Archeologico Regionale Antonino Salinas\" src=\"ISic001189_rightthreequarter_tiled-thumb.tif\"></a><a href=\"ISic001189_rightthreequarter.jpg\"><img title=\"Photo J. Prag, courtesy  Museo Archeologico Regionale Antonino Salinas\" src=\"ISic001189_rightthreequarter-thumb.jpg\"></a></div>  <div id=\"apparatus\"><h4>Apparatus criticus</h4><ul><li><span>  <span>Text based upon autopsy</span>  </span>; </li><li><span class=\"2\">2: <span>Salinas: [Κ]ίωτον; Kaibel: [Β]ίωτον; lapis: trace of upper eye of Β (contra Salinas, trace of K).</span>  </span></li></ul></div>  <div id=\"translation\"><h2>Italian translation</h2><p class=\"translation-author\">Norma Quagliana</p>  <p>Il damos (onora) Biotos figlio di Timandros per benevolenza</p>  </div>  <div id=\"translation\"><h2>English translation</h2><p class=\"translation-author\"><a href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0003-3819-8537\">Jonathan Prag</a></p>  <p>The people (honours) Biotos son of Timandros, for the sake of goodwill</p>  </div>  <div id=\"commentary\"><h2>commentary</h2>  <p>Notwithstanding the damage, it is clear that there was no ethnic included in the first part of the text, and the inscription appears complete. The name <span class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">Βίωτος</span> is also attested on tile and amphora stamps from southern Italy; no other form ending -ιωτος is known from the region.</p>  </div>  <div id=\"bibliography\"><h2>bibliography</h2>  <ul><li> Salinas NSA 1880 194 no. 4 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001392\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001392</a>  </li><li> Kaibel 1890 <a href=\"https://clio.columbia.edu/catalog/6873760\" target=\"_blank\">366</a>  <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072</a>  </li><li> Manni Piraino 1973 43 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000531\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000531</a>  </li><li> Consani 1996 125 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002071\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002071</a>  </li></ul>  <ul><li></li></ul>  </div>  <div id=\"handnote\"> <p>The letters are wide, well spaced and regular in form, and deeply incised. Alpha with straight bar; epsilon has short middle bar; kappa has full length arms; mu has vertical first and last, with middle strokes almost full height; omicron is full size; rho has large rounded head, closed; sigma has parallel top and bottom, and middle strokes almost full width; omega is closed, and slightly tear-drop shaped, with horizontal tails.</p> <p> Types list: <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Α-type1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Α type1</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Α-type1.3.html\" target=\"_blank\">Α type1.3</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ε-type2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ε type2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ε-type2.3.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ε type2.3</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ε-type2.3.1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ε type2.3.1</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ε-type2.3.2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ε type2.3.2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Κ-type2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Κ type2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Κ-type2.1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Κ type2.1</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Μ-type3.html\" target=\"_blank\">Μ type3</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Μ-type3.1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Μ type3.1</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ν-type2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ν type2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ν-type2.2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ν type2.2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ο-type1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ο type1</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ρ-type1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ρ type1</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ρ-type1.3.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ρ type1.3</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Σ-tyoe3.2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Σ tyoe3.2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Σ-type3.html\" target=\"_blank\">Σ type3</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Υ-type2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Υ type2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Υ-type2.1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Υ type2.1</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ω-type2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ω type2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ω-type2.2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ω type2.2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ω-type2.2.1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ω type2.2.1</a> </p> Line 1-3  25-30  Interlineation line 1 to 2  50  Interlineation line 2 to 3  40  </div><div id=\"license\"> Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence. </div>",
